results.question: How long did you work at Nurtur?
results.answer:
I have worked at Nurtur, operating as BriefYourMarket.com, for over two years now, starting in July 2022. During my time here, I have taken on the role of a full stack developer, and my focus has primarily been on developing production systems that are built to last. This involves a deep engagement with various technologies, especially in React and TypeScript, which I utilize extensively for creating internal dashboards that enhance our operational efficiency.

One of the significant projects I'm currently involved in is the Nexus project, which showcases my commitment to building robust and scalable applications. Additionally, I've also contributed to the Email Editor, a major team collaboration initiative aimed at rebuilding the core company product. This project focuses on enhancing our drag-and-drop email template functionality, making it more user-friendly and efficient for our clients. Working on these projects has allowed me to refine my skills in both front-end and back-end development, ensuring that I can effectively contribute to all aspects of our systems.

Throughout my time at Nurtur, I've been dedicated to not only delivering high-quality software but also ensuring that our products meet the evolving needs of our users. My role involves collaborating with cross-functional teams, gathering requirements, and implementing features that provide real value. I take pride in thoroughly documenting my work to facilitate a smooth transition, especially as I approach the end of my notice period, which is four weeks. This commitment to documentation is crucial for maintaining continuity and ensuring future developers can build upon the work we've done. 

Overall, my experience at Nurtur has been transformative, allowing me to grow as a developer while contributing to meaningful projects that impact the company's success.
